        <prompt>What was the significance of the Bessemer process in the 1870s?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Made steel production faster and cheaper</option>
            <option letter="b">Improved railroad construction techniques</option>
            <option letter="c">Created new farming methods</option>
            <option letter="d">Developed telegraph systems</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Bessemer process revolutionized steel production by making it significantly faster and cheaper, enabling the rapid growth of American industry and railroad construction.</explanation>
