    <question number="2">
        <prompt>What sparked the Great Railroad Strike of 1877?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Wage cuts by the Baltimore & Ohio Railroad</option>
            <option letter="b">Poor working conditions in factories</option>
            <option letter="c">Immigration restrictions</option>
            <option letter="d">New railroad regulations</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Great Railroad Strike of 1877 began when the B&O Railroad cut wages by 10%, leading to the first major national strike in U.S. history.</explanation>
