    <question number="3">
        <prompt>How did John D. Rockefeller create Standard Oil's monopoly?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Through horizontal and vertical integration</option>
            <option letter="b">Government subsidies</option>
            <option letter="c">Foreign investments</option>
            <option letter="d">Railroad construction</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Rockefeller built Standard Oil's monopoly through horizontal integration (buying competitors) and vertical integration (controlling all aspects of production and distribution).</explanation>
    </question>
    <question number="4">
        <prompt>What was the purpose of the Pendleton Civil Service Act of 1883?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To end the spoils system in federal hiring</option>
            <option letter="b">To regulate railroad rates</option>
            <option letter="c">To break up monopolies</option>
            <option letter="d">To protect labor unions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Pendleton Act established the civil service system, replacing the spoils system with merit-based hiring for federal jobs.</explanation>
